story.title: The Children - Episode 3
story.storyDescription: Someone throws a brick through Kiera's window. On the attached note, it says: GIVE BACK OUR CHILDREN.

messages.text: Keira locks the door to the basement behind her before she descends the steps.
Her phone lights up with a text from Doug.
I‚Äôm almost there ‚Äî had to park a few blocks away. Where are you?
In the basement. It wasn‚Äôt safe. People are breaking into our home.
Shit. Wait ‚Äî I see the police up ahead.
I‚Äôll tell them you‚Äôre going to come out peacefully and cooperate. Stay put, okay?
Before Keira can reply, a text pops up from an unknown number.
Just checking in. I‚Äôm not sure how long I have.
Is the mob under control?
Wait ‚Äî who is this?
Calvin.
I‚Äôm safe. For now. But don‚Äôt talk to police yet.
And whatever you do, do NOT go into the boiler room.
Why are you texting me from all these different numbers?
What are you talking about?
Keira sends the unknown number a screenshot of her text conversation with the restricted number.
What the hell is that?
It‚Äôs not you?!
No!
Maybe it‚Äôs the person coming to pick you up‚Ä¶
They called me ‚Äúhoney.‚Äù It‚Äôs like they were purposely trying to trick me.
Hide.
I‚Äôm going to find out what‚Äôs happening.
Calvin, I‚Äôm not budging. Not until you tell me what‚Äôs going on.
How do I even know this is you?
I said this to you before, Keira ‚Äî I don‚Äôt have much time.
Please trust me a little bit longer. I‚Äôll tell you as soon as I can. I promise.
I just need you to know I meant to do the right thing.
You mean, even though the news says you kidnapped children?
They‚Äôre wrong.
I need to go.
Someone was supposed to meet you in the workroom.
Was?
Stay hidden in the basement.
I love you.
Wait ‚Äî the whole house is surrounded. How can anyone get in?
It‚Äôs too hard to explain. I don‚Äôt have enough time.
Please trust me.
Cal‚Ä¶
There‚Äôs one thing you should know.
I wasn‚Äôt sure how to tell you.
Tell me what?
I‚Äôm not really a pediatrician.
WHAT THE HELL?
What do you mean you‚Äôre not a pediatrician?
Calvin?
Answer me.
But Calvin doesn‚Äôt reply.
A few minutes later, Kiera gets a text from Doug.
I‚Äôm trying to get to the police so you can get out. But they‚Äôre giving a statement.
There‚Äôs something you need to see.
I don‚Äôt think I can take much more.
You really need to see this.
Doug sends her a video of a crying couple with a young child. The child looks scary‚Äî
There‚Äôs an angry look on his face, like he wants to kill someone.
What the hell is this?
That‚Äôs what‚Äôs going on right now.
That kid looks scary.
Where are you?
Hiding.
Something‚Äôs really not right.
Keira hears a soft noise from the boiler room.
She strains to figure out what it is‚Äî
Is it the pipes from the boiler room?
No. She‚Äôs pretty sure it‚Äôs something else‚Ä¶
Maybe it‚Äôs in my head, but I swore I heard someone calling for help.
I‚Äôm going into the boiler room.
Keira, wait for the police.
But someone needs help. I‚Äôm positive.
I‚Äôm going in, whether you like it or not.
If you do, promise me you‚Äôll keep texting me along the way. I‚Äôm worried‚Äî
I want to know where you are and what‚Äôs happening.
Okay. It‚Äôs dark and really filthy in here‚Ä¶
There are a lot of wrappers and empty cans all over the floor.
I think this is where the missing food from the emergency cupboard went‚Ä¶
That‚Äôs weird. Why would someone steal food?
I don‚Äôt know.
Wait ‚Äî I hear something.
Something?
What is it?
Screaming.
It‚Äôs faint, but‚Äî
I‚Äôm absolutely positive someone‚Äôs screaming.
That‚Äôs it. I‚Äôm getting a police officer right now. Don‚Äôt go any further.
Before she can reply to Doug, a few messages from the restricted number pop up.
Where are you?
I‚Äôm in the workroom but you‚Äôre not here.
Keira hesitates before she texts.
Maybe she can trick this person into giving her more information.
Why did you want to meet in the workroom?
There‚Äôs a secret exit in there. It leads to the sewers‚Äî
So we can escape.
Keira pauses. There‚Äôs a secret exit to the sewers?
In her home?
Where are you taking me?
Somewhere safe.
When‚Äôs our anniversary?
What?
When‚Äôs our anniversary?
We don‚Äôt have time for games.
This isn‚Äôt a game.
I need to know it‚Äôs you.
Just come to the work room.
Keira switches her texts back to Doug.
Are the police with you?
Yeah. What‚Äôs wrong?
I think I‚Äôm in danger.
What? Did someone get inside the house?
I don‚Äôt know. But someone‚Äôs been texting me pretending to be Calvin.
I asked him when our anniversary is, but he didn‚Äôt know it. It‚Äôs not him.
What? I‚Äôm telling the police. Don‚Äôt move.
Keira notices some planks hiding an opening in the wall.
She takes a picture of it and sends it to Doug.
Then she pulls the planks away from the opening. She gasps.
There‚Äôs a network of secret tunnels running in and out of her basement.
She takes a photo and sends it to Doug as well.
The person who pretended to be Calvin said something about a secret exit.
They were right. I can‚Äôt believe it.
Don‚Äôt go in that tunnel!
Could it actually be Calvin texting me?
He wouldn‚Äôt forget your anniversary.
I might not trust him now, but I know he‚Äôd never forget that.
But why is someone pretending to be him?
What do they want? Who could it be?
I think I might know.
Really?
I‚Äôm not supposed to say.
Especially since this isn‚Äôt a secure line.
I don‚Äôt understand. Are you trying to say you actually know what‚Äôs going on?
I‚Äôm so sorry.
You lied to me? Seriously?
My husband is missing.
There are apparently hidden tunnels in my house.
I can hear people SCREAMING, and you‚Äôre keeping information from me?!
Why the hell won‚Äôt you tell me what‚Äôs going on?
Because I‚Äôve been instructed not to tell you.
By who?
The government.
